<plot>A cinematic, documentary examination of efforts to save the Chesapeake Bay through the eyes of three separate yet mutually dependent industries; blue crabs, farmers, and oyster aquaculturists. These different perspectives ultimately show how all the life in and around the Bay is connected, and that only when we all act together can we bring back the vitality of old to these now troubled waters.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?165212</url></doc>
